intro: Oenanthe australis, commonly known as the Australian cow-weed, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It is a member of the Apiaceae family, which includes carrots and parsley, and is characterized by its finely divided leaves and small, white flowers. The plant typically grows in moist, open habitats such as swampy areas and riverbanks. It has a fibrous root system and produces small, dry fruits that contain seeds. Oenanthe australis is often found in wetland environments and is adapted to tolerate waterlogged soils.
